#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.1:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Bālavagga"
msgstr "1. Fools"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Bhayasutta"
msgstr "1. Perils"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.101"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "an3.1:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "an3.1:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "an3.1:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an3.1:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

#. VAR: Bhadante → bhaddante (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an3.1:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "an3.1:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.1:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Yāni kānici, bhikkhave, bhayāni uppajjanti sabbāni tāni bālato uppajjanti, "
"no paṇḍitato."
msgstr ""
"“Whatever dangers there are, all come from the foolish, not from the astute."

# Upaddava and upasagga appear at AN 3.1, in a parallel at MN 115, and upaddava recurs in related passages at MN 122 and SN 16.8. See too Ss 8. In each case they seem to be a synonym of bhaya in the sense of “danger”, which in both upaddava and upasagga is related to the basic sense of “being rushed upon by something”. At MN 122 it is better to read in this sense rather than “undoing”; the undoing comes later. Notably, both upaddava and upasagga are terms for an eclipse, and possibly convey an echo of “ill-omened”. I translate “peril “and” hazard”.
msgctxt "an3.1:2.2"
msgid "Ye keci upaddavā uppajjanti sabbe te bālato uppajjanti, no paṇḍitato."
msgstr ""
"Whatever perils there are, all come from the foolish, not from the astute."

msgctxt "an3.1:2.3"
msgid "Ye keci upasaggā uppajjanti sabbe te bālato uppajjanti, no paṇḍitato."
msgstr ""
"Whatever hazards there are, all come from the foolish, not from the astute."

#. VAR: Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, naḷāgārā vā tiṇāgārā vā → naḷāgāro vā tiṇāgāro vā (bj)
#. VAR: aggi mutto → aggimukko (bj) | aggi mukko (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.1:2.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, naḷāgārā vā tiṇāgārā vā aggi mutto kūṭāgārānipi "
"ḍahati ullittāvalittāni nivātāni phusitaggaḷāni pihitavātapānāni;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like a fire that spreads from a hut made of reeds or grass, and burns "
"down even a bungalow, plastered inside and out, draft-free, with latches "
"fastened and windows shuttered."

msgctxt "an3.1:2.5"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yāni kānici bhayāni uppajjanti sabbāni tāni bālato "
"uppajjanti, no paṇḍitato."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, whatever dangers there are, all come from the foolish, not "
"from the astute."

msgctxt "an3.1:2.6"
msgid "Ye keci upaddavā uppajjanti sabbe te bālato uppajjanti, no paṇḍitato."
msgstr ""
"Whatever perils there are, all come from the foolish, not from the astute."

msgctxt "an3.1:2.7"
msgid "Ye keci upasaggā uppajjanti sabbe te bālato uppajjanti, no paṇḍitato."
msgstr ""
"Whatever hazards there are, all come from the foolish, not from the astute."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.1:3.1"
msgid "Iti kho, bhikkhave, sappaṭibhayo bālo, appaṭibhayo paṇḍito."
msgstr "So, the fool is dangerous, but the astute person is safe."

msgctxt "an3.1:3.2"
msgid "Saupaddavo bālo, anupaddavo paṇḍito."
msgstr "The fool is perilous, but the astute person is not."

msgctxt "an3.1:3.3"
msgid "Saupasaggo bālo, anupasaggo paṇḍito."
msgstr "The fool is hazardous, but the astute person is not."

msgctxt "an3.1:3.4"
msgid ""
"Natthi, bhikkhave, paṇḍitato bhayaṃ, natthi paṇḍitato upaddavo, natthi "
"paṇḍitato upasaggo."
msgstr "There’s no danger, peril, or hazard that comes from the astute."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.1:4.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, evaṃ sikkhitabbaṃ:"
msgstr "So you should train like this:"

msgctxt "an3.1:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘yehi tīhi dhammehi samannāgato bālo veditabbo te tayo dhamme "
"abhinivajjetvā, yehi tīhi dhammehi samannāgato paṇḍito veditabbo te tayo "
"dhamme samādāya vattissāmā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘We will reject the three things by which a fool is known, and we will "
"undertake and follow the three things by which an astute person is known.’"

msgctxt "an3.1:4.3"
msgid "Evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti."
msgstr "That’s how you should train.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.1:4.4"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
